name: 2.Data Description and Preparation
content:
Data Description :


AP-AR Cashflow Forecasting Data :

  • Below are the three important datasets, which is used in Model Training and Evaluation.

1. AR Payment Details :

  • Sales_Order_Number: Unique ID for a sales order.
  • Sales_Order_Date: Date on when the sales order was created.
  • Sales_Invoice_Number: Unique ID for the sales invoice.
  • Invoice_Date: Date on when the invoice was issued.
  • Customer_Number: Unique ID for the customer.
  • Deposit_Date: Date on when the deposit/payment was received.
  • Max_Due_Date: Latest payment due date for the invoice.
  • Line_Number: Sequential number for items on the invoice.
  • Line_Item: Specific product or service on the invoice.
  • Receipt_Number: Unique ID for the payment receipt.
  • Receipt_Status: Current status of the payment receipt.
  • Receipt_Date: Date the payment was received.
  • Currency_Code: Currency used in the transaction.
  • Receipt_Amount_USD: Payment amount in US Dollars.

2. AP Payment Details :

  • PO_Number: Unique ID for the purchase order.
  • Supplier_Number: Unique ID for the supplier.
  • Ordered_Date: Date the purchase order was placed.
  • Due_Date: Date the payment or delivery is due.
  • Order_Currency_Code: Currency used in the purchase order.
  • Order_Amount_USD: Total order amount in US Dollars.
  • Completed_Flag: Status indicating if the order is completed or not.
  • Invoice_Number: Unique ID for the invoice.
  • Invoice_Date: Date the invoice was issued.
  • Payment_Date: Date the payment was made.
  • Line_Number: Sequential number for items on the invoice.
  • Line_Item: Specific product in the purchase order

3. Payroll :

  • Payment_Date: Date the payment was made.
  • Amount_USD: Payment amount in US Dollars.
  • Payment_Dt: Date of the payment transaction.
  • Payment_Dt_year: Year of the payment transaction.
  • Payment_Dt_month: Month of the payment transaction.
  • Year_Month: Combined year and month of the payment.


Distribution of continuous values of receipt_amount_usd :

  • The table outlines the distribution of receipt amounts in U.S. dollars across various ranges from $180 to $2538.
  • It shows the number of receipts within each range, highlighting significant concentrations at the lowest and highest ranges with no receipts in the $415.80 to $651.60 range.



Distribution of continuous values of order_amount_usd :

  • The majority of orders (29,753) fall in the lowest range of $13.0 to $381.2, while the counts decrease significantly as the order amount increases.
  • The highest range ($3326.8 to $3695.0) has the fewest orders, with only 6 recorded.
  • This suggests that most orders are of lower value, with a steep decline in higher-value orders.


Histogram of Receipt Amount :

  • The histogram illustrates the distribution of receipt amounts, with the highest concentration in the $180.0 to $415.8 range, where more than 50,000 receipts are recorded.
  • As the receipt amount increases, the frequency steadily decreases, with fewer than 5,000 receipts in the range of $2302.2 to $2538.0, the lowest category.



Histogram of Order Amount :

  • The histogram shows most orders are between $13.0 and $381.2, with about 30,000 orders in this range.
  • As the order amount increases, the number of orders drops quickly.
  • Very few orders are above $1854, and almost none in the highest range of $3326.8 to $3695.0.


Account Receivable Dataset :

  • The below dataset is of Account Receivable Dataset
  • The dataset provides a structured view of financial transactions, tracking the progress of orders from sales to payment.
  • It helps in monitoring the status of accounts receivable and ensuring that all due payments are made on time.
  • It reflects when a company made a sale and recorded it as receivable, meaning the company expects to receive payment from Customer.
  • This data is from the perspective of the seller.



Account Payable Dataset :

  • This dataset helps monitor outstanding liabilities to suppliers and track the status of payments for different purchase orders.
  • It provides an organized view of payable transactions, ensuring that payment deadlines are met and suppliers are compensated appropriately.
  • It tracks when the company made a purchase and recorded it as payable, meaning the company expects to pay for goods.
  • This data is from the perspective of the buyer.



Sales Order Year Distribution :

  • The below graph is about distribution of Sales Orders over the years.
  • It provides a visual representation of how the number of sales orders fluctuated over time.
  • Here the y-axis represents Total number of Sales Orders to the customers.


Order Year Distribution :

  • The below graph represents the total number of Orders to the suppliers made over the years.
  • It provides a visual representation of how the number of orders to suppliers fluctuated over time.
  • Here the Y-axis represents the total number of orders to the suppliers.





Data Preparation for Cashflow Forecasting :


1. Handling Missing Values :

Remove missing values in critical columns are identified and handled through:

  • NaN Identification: Rows with NaN values in key financial columns are flagged for correction.
  • Imputation or Deletion: Depending on the nature of the missing data, missing values are replaced with value 0.

3. Data Transformation :

To make the data suitable for analysis, several transformations are applied:

  • Date Formatting: Ensuring that date fields are correctly parsed and indexed. Dates are converted to a standard format (e.g., YYYY-MM-DD) to maintain consistency across datasets.
  • DataType Formatting: Ensuring that all the columns are having correct Datatype, so that other operations on them could be easily performed.

4. Data Validation

Once the data is cleaned and transformed, validation checks are performed to ensure the accuracy of the forecast:

  • Outlier Detection: Any unusually high or low values are flagged as outliers to prevent them from skewing the forecast.
